explanation: The problem can be solved by repeatedly subtracting 1 or dividing by 2 from n until it becomes 0. If n is odd, subtract 1; otherwise, divide by 2. This approach takes advantage of the fact that powers of 2 are the only numbers that can be subtracted from n to make it 0. The time complexity is O(log n) because the number of operations is proportional to the number of times we can divide n by 2 before it becomes 0.

